00:37:01.080 --> 00:37:05.190
is when the rich decide to
go one way or the other.

00:37:05.190 --> 00:37:07.945
And I'm just curious
to hear your thoughts.

00:37:07.945 --> 00:37:09.820
FREDERICK "SHAD" ROWE:
On accumulating money?

00:37:14.040 --> 00:37:16.650
AUDIENCE: Philanthropy,
or you know,

00:37:16.650 --> 00:37:20.730
investment in change in the
context of larger good--

00:37:20.730 --> 00:37:22.372
how do investors think about it?

00:37:22.372 --> 00:37:24.580
FREDERICK "SHAD" ROWE: I
think about it all the time.

00:37:24.580 --> 00:37:27.710
And I don't--

00:37:27.710 --> 00:37:31.770
I'm usually disappointed by
what I discover about what

00:37:31.770 --> 00:37:33.730
was really happening.

00:37:33.730 --> 00:37:35.504
I mean, you know people
get old, and they

00:37:35.504 --> 00:37:37.170
want to have hospitals
named after them,

00:37:37.170 --> 00:37:39.279
and they want to
invest in health care.

00:37:39.279 --> 00:37:41.820
